{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 16:12:57.349392", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission accepted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"pc_0_1\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"link_high_packet_corruption\"]\n\nDiagnosis rationale (brief):\n- Control-plane (BGP/routes) is healthy across leaf/spine/super-spine.\n- Data-plane reachability failing only for pc_0_1.\n- tc on pc_0_1:eth0 shows netem qdisc configured with corrupt 60% — direct cause of high packet loss.\n- Leaf router for that subnet is healthy and advertising the network; therefore the impairment is host-local.\n\nIf you want, I can provide commands to remove the netem qdisc on pc_0_1, run packet captures, or gather additional debugging output.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2038, "output_tokens": 161, "total_tokens": 2199, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
